98
00:06:08,488 --> 00:06:09,184
You are kidding

99
00:06:11,574 --> 00:06:13,371
You remind me of something

100
00:06:14,512 --> 00:06:17,332
How about Sumie Higuchi, who used to be in the secretarial section?

101
00:06:17,442 --> 00:06:18,449
She is fine

102
00:06:18,809 --> 00:06:20,019
She does bar business in Tsukishima

103
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:21,356
Oh I see

104
00:06:22,012 --> 00:06:23,973
I thought she got married

105
00:06:24,153 --> 00:06:26,535
It's a beautiful bar in that area

106
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,168
I see

107
00:06:27,699 --> 00:06:29,442
She must have found a good patron

108
00:06:30,129 --> 00:06:31,567
It might be so

109
00:06:32,012 --> 00:06:33,567
You have good memory

110
00:06:34,082 --> 00:06:34,653
About her

111
00:06:34,895 --> 00:06:36,192
I won't forget her

112
00:06:36,973 --> 00:06:40,863
Shortly after joining the company I made a printing mistake.
She helped me out

113
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,684
Oh yeah, I remember that

114
00:06:50,098 --> 00:06:51,262
By the way,Hiyama-san

115
00:06:51,887 --> 00:06:54,473
I know it's been a while since we've seen each other, but it's hard to say...

116
00:06:55,785 --> 00:06:58,332
Can I borrow 1000 or 2000 yen from you?

117
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:03,199
Well...I lost a bet on a horse race

118
00:07:04,059 --> 00:07:07,535
I'm running out of money as opposed to earning an allowance

119
00:07:09,481 --> 00:07:10,910
Have you always liked horse racing?

120
00:07:11,207 --> 00:07:12,262
I like it

121
00:07:13,317 --> 00:07:13,871
Here it is

122
00:07:14,535 --> 00:07:15,598
Thank you very much

123
00:07:15,949 --> 00:07:16,949
I'll return you soon

124
00:07:17,496 --> 00:07:18,457
Where do you live?

125
00:07:18,551 --> 00:07:20,410
Don't worry.
You can see me whenever you are free

126
00:07:20,435 --> 00:07:21,238
I see

127
00:07:22,098 --> 00:07:22,817
Thank you very much

128
00:07:38,621 --> 00:07:39,278
Yes

129
00:07:41,543 --> 00:07:42,207
Oh you

130
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:43,168
No work today?

131
00:07:43,324 --> 00:07:46,176
I was supposed to work but I have overtime every day so..

132
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:47,676
I'm so tired, got headache

133
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:48,481
Are you OK?

134
00:07:48,707 --> 00:07:49,153
Yes

135
00:07:49,715 --> 00:07:50,840
You should take a rest

136
00:07:50,949 --> 00:07:51,981
Thank you

137
00:07:52,285 --> 00:07:54,121
There is a blanket in closet

138
00:07:54,176 --> 00:07:54,590
Thanks

139
00:07:55,113 --> 00:07:56,043
Take care

140
00:07:56,637 --> 00:07:57,848
I'm going out

141
00:07:58,145 --> 00:07:59,418
Take care of yourself

142
00:07:59,465 --> 00:07:59,910
Yes

143
00:08:01,090 --> 00:08:04,082
There are some bread there.
You can eat if you are hungry

144
00:08:04,223 --> 00:08:04,481
Um

145
00:08:31,403 --> 00:08:33,160
Can you come over here,Hiyama?

146
00:08:38,176 --> 00:08:40,277
It's awful that you transferred me without even asking me what I wanted

147
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,606
If you don't like it, it's company policy to let you leave the company

148
00:08:44,113 --> 00:08:45,379
You mean you want me to leave this company?

149
00:08:45,879 --> 00:08:47,434
If you refuse the transfer, there is no way to ask you leave this company

150
00:08:49,199 --> 00:08:50,512
You idiot!

151
00:08:53,129 --> 00:08:54,231
Stop it!

152
00:08:55,270 --> 00:08:56,004
Let me go!

153
00:08:58,817 --> 00:09:00,293
I will leave this company!

154
00:09:07,326 --> 00:09:08,686
I will leave this company!

155
00:09:21,780 --> 00:09:22,912
Mmmmm...

156
00:09:25,092 --> 00:09:26,139
Kashiwagi-san?

157
00:09:28,272 --> 00:09:29,116
Kashiwagi-san?

158
00:09:29,217 --> 00:09:29,944
Mmmm

159
00:09:31,233 --> 00:09:32,053
Kashiwagi-san?

160
00:09:33,569 --> 00:09:33,959
Yes

161
00:09:39,741 --> 00:09:40,225
Hi!

162
00:09:41,991 --> 00:09:42,741
Are you kashiwagi-san?

163
00:09:43,186 --> 00:09:43,561
Yes

164
00:09:43,881 --> 00:09:47,616
Well..This resident list lists only one person, Eiko Kashiwagi

165
00:09:48,092 --> 00:09:49,998
What kind of relationship do you have with her?

166
00:09:53,091 --> 00:09:53,708
Your name?

167
00:09:54,561 --> 00:09:55,241
Kenji Hiyama

168
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:56,241
Address?

169
00:09:56,514 --> 00:09:57,030
Address?

170
00:09:57,694 --> 00:09:59,553
The police won't check your family register now.

171
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:01,475
You ask me my name and address.
What you will do then?

172
00:10:01,655 --> 00:10:03,264
This is not checking your family register

173
00:10:03,616 --> 00:10:04,849
Information network in the jurisdiction...

174
00:10:04,873 --> 00:10:06,170
I am not shady

175
00:10:06,686 --> 00:10:07,787
I'm not a thief

176
00:10:07,873 --> 00:10:08,811
No No do not misunderstand me

177
00:10:09,522 --> 00:10:11,280
Then I understand.
Excuse me

178
00:10:15,959 --> 00:10:16,998
How dare you

179
00:10:19,646 --> 00:10:20,545
Ah...

180
00:10:23,069 --> 00:10:23,701
Awww

181
00:10:25,178 --> 00:10:26,326
Do not disturb me

182
00:10:26,686 --> 00:10:27,451
Who's there?

183
00:10:27,756 --> 00:10:28,803
I'm Miyagawa

184
00:10:29,303 --> 00:10:30,100
Miyagawa?

185
00:10:33,365 --> 00:10:34,771
Oh you

186
00:10:35,482 --> 00:10:36,365
How did you know here?

187
00:10:36,451 --> 00:10:40,537
Mr.Yoshida of your company told me you probably stay here

188
00:10:40,741 --> 00:10:41,444
Yoshida said that?

189
00:10:41,569 --> 00:10:41,998
Yes

190
00:10:43,084 --> 00:10:44,858
Can I come in?

191
00:10:45,725 --> 00:10:46,116
Please

192
00:10:49,451 --> 00:10:50,537
Please take your seat

193
00:10:54,826 --> 00:10:56,467
What a nice room it is!

194
00:10:57,545 --> 00:10:58,967
Is this the home of your future wife?

195
00:11:00,264 --> 00:11:01,459
Yoshida also said that?

196
00:11:01,725 --> 00:11:02,037
Ha?

197
00:11:04,162 --> 00:11:05,069
Please make yourself at home

198
00:11:06,943 --> 00:11:07,764
Why you have visited me?

199
00:11:08,990 --> 00:11:10,966
Thank you for the other day

200
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:12,889
I'm sorry I don't have a envelop for the money

201
00:11:13,310 --> 00:11:16,084
You didn't have to come all this way

202
00:11:17,154 --> 00:11:17,443
Thanks

203
00:11:18,146 --> 00:11:18,826
Ah wait!

204
00:11:19,740 --> 00:11:20,975
You don't have to check the bill?

205
00:11:21,264 --> 00:11:21,717
What?

206
00:11:22,685 --> 00:11:24,334
There are just two bills so I don't need to check

207
00:11:24,857 --> 00:11:27,209
Have you noticed anything different?

208
00:11:28,826 --> 00:11:30,193
I have not noticed anything different

209
00:11:30,404 --> 00:11:31,951
Can you compare with other 1000yen bill?

210
00:11:32,396 --> 00:11:32,974
What?

211
00:11:48,131 --> 00:11:49,631
You haven't noticed yet?

212
00:11:49,982 --> 00:11:52,553
There is a difference from the other 1000yen bill

213
00:11:59,553 --> 00:12:00,701
There is no number!

214
00:12:01,662 --> 00:12:03,115
What the hell is this?

215
00:12:04,006 --> 00:12:05,998
A printing error at the mint?

216
00:12:06,248 --> 00:12:07,100
No way!

217
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:10,412
A bill without numbers won't make it to the world

218
00:12:10,834 --> 00:12:15,631
I'm sorry to have to say this but Nowadays, bills are made by the Printing Bureau, not the Mint.

219
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:17,271
You are right

220
00:12:18,411 --> 00:12:20,153
so Are these counterfeit bills?

221
00:12:20,475 --> 00:12:22,185
Yes that's right

222
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:26,662
There's a watermark on the bill.

223
00:12:27,014 --> 00:12:28,490
It's easy to make it

224
00:12:28,842 --> 00:12:32,420
For example,If you put a half sheet of paper on top of the tempura

225
00:12:32,850 --> 00:12:34,889
The oil soaks into it, making it look translucent

226
00:12:35,428 --> 00:12:36,209
That's it

227
00:12:37,912 --> 00:12:39,833
So..You made this

228
00:12:40,084 --> 00:12:42,225
How is this?
It's hard to notice,isn't it?

229
00:12:43,021 --> 00:12:46,029
Making counterfeit money is a serious crime.

230
00:12:46,310 --> 00:12:50,600
Making counterfeit money for use is punishable by life imprisonment or more than three years

231
00:12:51,631 --> 00:12:55,232
Even if it's not intended for use, people don't think so

232
00:12:56,154 --> 00:12:58,560
What happen if someone report you a police?

233
00:12:58,717 --> 00:12:59,568
Don't worry

234
00:13:00,381 --> 00:13:03,256
You are the only person I showed this

235
00:13:03,529 --> 00:13:04,342
Only me?

236
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:06,607
What the hell is this?

237
00:13:10,053 --> 00:13:12,318
Actually,I need your wisdom

238
00:13:12,889 --> 00:13:13,475
My wisdom?

239
00:13:14,350 --> 00:13:15,443
I have a favor of you

240
00:13:17,592 --> 00:13:18,631
Can you?

241
00:13:19,412 --> 00:13:21,404
So you made this for use?

242
00:13:21,490 --> 00:13:25,334
I'll get back to you on that after you've consulted with me.

243
00:13:25,865 --> 00:13:26,716
How many bill have you made?

244
00:13:26,959 --> 00:13:29,037
I will tell you later

245
00:13:30,545 --> 00:13:32,889
But..it's hard to consult with you

246
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,131
I think I'm stuck.…

247
00:13:35,685 --> 00:13:37,779
I didn't know you'd come to me for help with something like this

248
00:13:37,896 --> 00:13:42,146
I've given it some thought, and I've told you

249
00:13:46,818 --> 00:13:50,607
Call me when you've made up your mind

250
00:13:51,990 --> 00:13:52,420
Please

251
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:06,951
Actually,I need your wisdom

252
00:14:12,193 --> 00:14:13,529
This is a consultation

253
00:14:14,928 --> 00:14:17,404
Call me when you've made up your mind

254
00:14:22,115 --> 00:14:24,373
Oh you forgot something

255
00:14:24,685 --> 00:14:25,459
Your cigarette

256
00:14:26,685 --> 00:14:27,248
Thank you

257
00:14:38,256 --> 00:14:38,920
This guy

258
00:14:39,904 --> 00:14:42,396
I first met him at the race track.

259
00:14:43,123 --> 00:14:45,935
He came to see me after a few days,then asked me for a drink

260
00:14:46,232 --> 00:14:47,498
I like drinking

261
00:14:48,615 --> 00:14:50,295
I drunk with him 6 or 7 times since then

262
00:14:51,068 --> 00:14:54,389
But He told me one night that he had a lucrative job for me

263
00:14:54,701 --> 00:14:56,381
That job was making counterfeit paper money?

264
00:14:57,178 --> 00:14:59,678
Yes, he asked me to Print 10,000 bills with 1000 yen bill

265
00:15:00,014 --> 00:15:00,842
It means 10 million yen?

266
00:15:01,107 --> 00:15:02,365
Of course I refused it

267
00:15:03,279 --> 00:15:05,584
I take pride in my printing work

268
00:15:06,310 --> 00:15:08,842
It's easy to make counterfeit money

269
00:15:10,178 --> 00:15:13,623
I've always heard that making counterfeit money is not a worthwhile crime

270
00:15:14,913 --> 00:15:19,686
But he said it's a crime if you make it yourself and use it yourself.

271
00:15:20,828 --> 00:15:22,156
He said you just make it

272
00:15:22,804 --> 00:15:25,890
He said He will buy them at real 4 million yen if I make the fake 10 million yen bills

273
00:15:26,578 --> 00:15:28,390
Then we cut off our ties

274
00:15:28,953 --> 00:15:31,085
He has nothing to do with the one who uses it

275
00:15:31,859 --> 00:15:35,898
He said you can get real 4 million yen

276
00:15:37,523 --> 00:15:42,156
